article.headline: N. Colorado 67, Wyoming 53
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Devon Beitzel scored 20 points as Northern Colorado defeated Wyoming for the first time in 73 years, winning 67-53 on Tuesday night. Chris Kaba added 15 points and eight rebounds for Northern Colorado (1-0). The Bears, coming off their best record in school history at 25-8, had lost 20 consecutive games to Wyoming. Francisco Cruz had 13 points for Wyoming (1-1), which last lost to the Bears in 1937. The Cowboys, who still lead the series 49-17, didn't make a field goal until Djibril Thiam's rebound basket nearly eight minutes into the game. Wyoming managed only eight field goals and 35 percent shooting in the first half.
